  "text": "For each skin specimen a 12 × 12 mm mosaic was created, such that the magnification is equivalent to that of a standard lowpower 2× view of optical microscopes. It took 150 seconds to display each 12 × 12 mm panel and 20 additional seconds for the subsequent image stitching. The instrumentation, imaging, and technical details have been described by Gareau et al. [CITATION_1] ",
